column1: **The RINSE 1YCM turned slightly pink in the anaerobic chamber when most of it had been used up. It was pink when used for formulation 1
Bottles 3'A,B,C,D placed in beckman centrifuge at 9:30 for 15min at 5000rpms and 4C
Cell pellet rinsed with 20mL of RINSE 1YCM
Cells centrigued in rotana for 15min at 6000rcf and 4C at 10:10.
Coatings placed in vacuum chamber at 11:30.
Tubes placed in respective RH bottles.
All bottles were flushed with argon at 10psi for 10 minutes
**Note the RINSE 1YCM turned pink even before rehydrating the tubes, but changed back to neutral after being flushed with syngas.
Tubes A-E rehydrated with 4mL of RINSE
Tubes F,G,H rehydrated w/ 4mL of 2mL media
Tubes I,J,K rehydrated w/ 4mL of 4mL media
Tubes L-O rehydated with 4mL of 4mL media
All tubes flushed with syngas for 2min at 10psi.
All tubes placed in shaker at 2:25 at 50rpm & 37C
Samples taken from tubes A-L at 2:25 PM on 11/3/2015
Samples taken from tubes M-O at 3:00 PM on 11/3/2015
All tubes returned to shaker between and after samples were taken
Sampling 11/4/15 Samples taken from tubes at 8:35am
Tubes L,M,N,and O showed discoloration of the coating on the cell side of the paper. The cells seemed to have begun to turn black.
pH was measured of some of the tubes to test if the reducing agent was causing variance in pH

column3: Good pH range; samples made with 1mL CYS; these had highest reactivities
** Keep in mind -- aceatic acid production would cause pH to decrease
Cells reduced with 1mL CYS Na2S also had decent reactivity, but higher pH; Na2S raises the pH
pH of 2mL CYS Na2S samples is high; cells had lowest reactivity
